Program: Outlook
Title: 01/12/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00lskg0
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 5 Dec 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, two lives that were changed by the Santa Cruz massacre, which happened 20 years ago in Dili, East Timor. First, British film maker Max Stahl, who filmed the massacre and spread the news around the world. And also the country's first First Lady, Kirsty Sword Gusmao, who joined the country's struggle for independence after learning about the bloodshed in 1991. Show less